    "comment": "Rationale: Note: CB1R is a receptor that is predominantly presynaptic (see f.i. ticket #794).\n\nFig.3: \"Co-localization of SGIP1 with compartment-specific neuronal markers and CB1R in cultured cortical neurons\"\n- The SGIP1 protein co-localized with the axonal marker Tau1 as well as with anti-Bassoon antibodies, which label presynaptic portions of the neurites. Overlap in SGIP1 and Bassoon staining was observed. Co-localization of SGIP1 with the dendritic marker MAP2 only partially overlapped and we concluded that SGIP1 labeling is found on the presynaptic portions of afferent neurites. SGIP1 was found to be present (at least partially) in neuronal compartments in which CB1R was detected. Employing CB1R specific antibodies together with SGIP1 detection showed an overlapping punctuated pattern in MAP2-negative structures that corresponded to the presynaptic portions observed in anti-Bassoon labeling (Fig. 3A and B).\". Experimental description: - \"Rat embryonic cortical neurons E18 were isolated from Wistar rat brains\"\n- \"The cDNA coding for mouse SGIP1 was purchased from TrueClones (Origene Technologies, Inc., USA), ...\"",
